original: Lindskog, Johan Henrik, kyrkoherde, Axvall, f. 22/1/84 i Skara. G. 31 m. Andrea Thomaeus. Barn: Lisa f. 33. — Studrex. i Lund 03, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 04, teol. kand. i Upps. 10, prästv. i Skara 13. Res. t. Danm. Kommin. i N. Ving, Stenum, Skärv o. Skånings-Åsaka 22, kyrkoh. där sed. 38. Ordf. i kyrkoråd i N. Ving, Stenum, Skärv o. Skånings-Asaka, ordf. i N. Vings skoilråd o, Stenums kyrkostämma. Skr.: ’smärre upps. i olika publikationer.
translated: Lindskog, Johan Henrik, pastor, Axvall, born January 22, 1884 in Skara. Married in 1931 to Andrea Thomaeus. Children: Lisa, born in 1933. Studied at Lund University in 1903, graduated with a Bachelor of Theology in Lund in 1904, and obtained a Master's degree in Theology at Uppsala University in 1910. Ordained as a minister in Skara in 1913. Resided in Denmark for a period. Served as a curate in N. Ving, Stenum, Skärv, and Skånings-Åsaka from 1922, and as a pastor there from 1938. Chairman of the church council in N. Ving, Stenum, Skärv, and Skånings-Åsaka, as well as chairman of N. Vings school council and Stenums church assembly. Has written several minor essays in various publications.
